ior of the students in the public school system was terrible.  The structure was questionable after going to an open house and speaking to the teachers.  It seems to me that it was just a regular job and not a passion to teach.  We took our grandson out of public school and back into private. Now, for my grandchildren in public school.  Our grandson is in the fifth grade and loves to read.  His scored the highesst in the state for reading, math and science.  Does the public system consider advancing him?  No, this has been going on for since he started school.  He is so bored, and even told me  there aren't anymore books of interest for him in school anymore.  We have decided to also send him a private school as soon as he is able to test and interview. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1071" language="en" documentId="3063" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="gailnalei" date="Aug 29, 2013 7:47PM" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://living.msn.com/family-parenting/the-family-room-blog-post?post=ab228ffc-1e99-4b37-a7b8-0b6a4c3fb240" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="7" thumbsDown="0" origId="3063" notes="" title="Is it wrong to send kids to private school?"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1071"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>